    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>How Mrs. White Restrained Her Children</strong>&mdash;When the children will beg that they may go to this company or join that party of amusement, say to them: &ldquo;I cannot let you go, children; sit right down here, and I will tell you why. I am doing up work for eternity and for God. God has given you to me and entrusted you to my care. I am standing in the place of God to you, my children; therefore I must watch you as one who must give an account in the day of God. Do you want your mother&apos;s name written in the books of heaven as one who failed to do her duty to her children, as one who let the enemy come in and preoccupy the ground that I ought to have occupied? Children, I am going to tell you which is the right way, and then if you choose to turn away from your mother and go into the paths of wickedness, your mother will stand clear, but you will have to suffer for your own sins.&rdquo;",
